From 66089bb28cde0def01c07e061d8c1983e37f6bb2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fabio Paracchini <fparacchini@alteanet.it>
Date: Wed, 11 Mar 2026 12:40:10 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 17/21] feat(analytics): add cross-filter by model and user in
 admin dashboard
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Add user_id filter to get_message_count_by_model and get_token_usage_by_model
- Add model_id filter to get_message_count_by_user and get_token_usage_by_user
- Expose user_id param on /analytics/models and /analytics/tokens endpoints
- Expose model_id param on /analytics/users endpoint
- Update analytics API client (getModelAnalytics, getUserAnalytics, getTokenUsage)
- Dashboard: click a model row to filter User Activity table by that model
- Dashboard: click a user row to filter Model Usage table by that user
- Active filter shown as dismissible badge above each table
- Selected row highlighted in blue; → button still opens model detail modal
